    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Building It Is No Guarantee</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>John Zidziunas letter contends that building new arena for New Jersey Devils in Newark (NJ) will not guarantee that fans will come to watch games (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>Mayor Sharpe James must think he is Kevin Costner in the movie ''Field of Dreams.'' All he has to do is build a hockey arena in downtown Newark and paying customers will come! Where were those hockey fans when the Devils were losing millions of dollars in the Meadowlands? Didn't the build-first-ask-questions-later approach already fail (as Harvey Araton points out) when Newark went ahead with a downtown baseball stadium for the Newark Bears?</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>Mayor Sharpe James must think he is Kevin Costner in the movie ''Field of Dreams.'' All he has to do is build a hockey arena in downtown Newark and paying customers will come! Where were those hockey fans when the Devils were losing millions of dollars in the Meadowlands? Didn't the build-first-ask-questions-later approach already fail (as Harvey Araton points out) when Newark went ahead with a downtown baseball stadium for the Newark Bears?</p>
        <p>The proposed Newark arena isn't a dream. It's a nightmare -- a nightmare that the taxpayers of New Jersey's biggest city are going to have to pay for decades to come.</p>
        <p>JOHN ZIDZIUNAS  Newark</p>
        <p>The writer is district leader of Newark's East Ward, District 6.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
